body:
I'm using Verilator as part of a software for teaching digital design with the help of SystemVerilog, and we expect our students to not use any kind of inline logic net initialization.  Shown in the example below:

```
module asic (...);
    logic a;    // this is fine
    // logic a = 1;    // but this is not fine

    reg b = 1;  // this is fine since it is not a flip-flop

    always @(posedge clk, posedge rst)
    if (rst)
        a <= 0;
    else if (b)
        a <= ~a;
endmodule
```

The idea is that students will write designs intended to be ASIC-compatible, so naturally that would require that all registers that are part of flip-flops have a reset and not be initialized with a value using an initial block or inline initialization.  

I've been poring through the Verilator manual, but I can't seem to find a a related option.  How could I use Verilator to implement this check?
